{"questionId":"3125939","questionHtml":"<p>Huw travels in a straight line from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>. Calculate the time that Huw takes to complete this journey. Give your answer correct to the nearest minute.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/67e4e4e85c479bab6efddc13d864b07f30e2f6b8.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3007</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>27933</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>use of trigonometry to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HA</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AS</mi></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HA</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AS</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HA</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>39204</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AS</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>78408</mn><mo>…</mo></math>)</p>\n<p>use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>time</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>distance</mi><mi>speed</mi></mfrac></math> for either of their distances &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>time taken <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>AH</mi><mn>15</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>AS</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>649618</mn><mo>…</mo></math> (hours) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>38</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99712</mn><mo>…</mo></math> minutes)</p>\n<p>therefore <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn></math> (mins) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1FT</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Allow <em><strong>FT</strong></em>, within the question part, from their time in hours for the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>use of similar triangles to identify either length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>MA</mi></math> or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AN</mi></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>or</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>attempt to use Pythagoras for either triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AMH</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ANS</mi></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>AH</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>AS</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use Pythagoras for larger triangle &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>SH</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AH</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msqrt><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; <strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AS</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msqrt><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HA</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>39204</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AS</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>78408</mn><mo>…</mo></math>)</p>\n<p>use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>time</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>distance</mi><mi>speed</mi></mfrac></math> for either of THEIR distances &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>time taken <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>AH</mi><mn>15</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>AS</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>649618</mn><mo>…</mo></math> (hours) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>38</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99712</mn><mo>…</mo></math> minutes)</p>\n<p>therefore <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn></math> (mins) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1FT</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Allow <em><strong>FT</strong></em>, within the question part, from their time in hours for the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3125939","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.1a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Huw travels in a straight line from H to S. Calculate the time that Huw takes to complete this journey. Give your answer correct to the nearest minute.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}